HABITAT. — This species was found on mud under dead wood and rocks at the edge of ponds in the dry season (
Fig. 2A, B
). During the rainy season, the species always lives close to water and we collected them on submerged grasses, under shrubs on the edge of little water bodies. 

Phrynobatrachus latifrons

lives in tree and open savannahs, farm bush and agricultural areas. It avoids closed primary rainforest, but may be found in degraded rainforest (
Rödel 2000
; 

Kpan 
et al.
2014

; 
Onadeko 2016
; 
Rödel & Glos 2019
).
